    <note>Zhang(1) Hao(3) [26536] Both Renming Da cidian and funerary inscription for descendant, Gongyu [26541], identify him as a 6th generation descendant (7th by my count) of Liang [12239], but both Zhou Jiayou and XTS genealogical tables would make him a 9th (tenth by my count) descendant, which makes perfect chronological sense, whereas a 6th generation identification would make no sense whatever. One set of Hao(3)'s descendants remained in Sichuan, whereas his son, Yu (not in dateset), moved to Fangcheng county and became the ancestor of all the other distinguished Fanyang and Qinghe Zhang(1). XTS, 72C.1a-1b; Zhou Jiayou, 1.170; Renming Da cidian, p. 957.</note>
